ldd / listdatadirectory       Shows the location of the Axmud data directory
 
   Format:
      ;ldd                    Shows the directory
 
   Notes:
      Axmud stores all of its data files in a single directory (folder). The
         location of this directory varies from system to system, and also
         depends on how Axmud was installed.
      This command shows the location of Axmud's data directory. To change it,
         see the help for ';setdatadirectory'.
         
   User commands:
      ldd / listdatadir / listdatafolder / listdatadirectory
